#Text=Majuro
#Text=Majuro is the largest city and capital of the Marshall Islands .
#Text=The downtown area is located north of the airport on the eastern side of the main island .
#Text=It consists of the smaller towns Delap , Uliga and Darrit which are reside on islands linked by small stretches of land .
#Text=Get in
#Text=A boat dock is on the lagoon side of Uliga .
#Text=By plane
#Text=Amata Kabua International Airport ( MAJ ) is on the south side of the Majuro atoll .
#Text=United Airlines has thrice-weekly service from Honolulu as the first stop on its " island hopper " route which also serves the Federated States of Micronesia and Guam .

column1: #Text=Flights from Guam via FSM and Kwajalein are available on the remaining weekdays .
#Text=The island hopper flight stops at various atolls on the way to/from Guam makes for a scenic way to the destination .
#Text=Hotel transfers are usually available for free upon reservation .
#Text=Taxis from the airport to town are cheap as well ( around US$ 5 ) and it is customary to pick up additional passengers on the way .
#Text=There is only one road in Majuro .
#Text=If you are on a walk far away from the city center , police and other people will often give you a ride if they are going in the same direction .
#Text=Get around
#Text=The island can be explored by foot .
#Text=The only exception to this is Laura Beach .
#Text=Taxis are cheap ( $ 0.75 ) as long you stay east of the airport .
#Text=To further reduce costs cab sharing is common .
#Text=Getting to Laura Beach by taxi is expensive , but buses make the round trip to Laura 6 days a week ( not on Sundays ) for $ 2 , departing from the RRE parking lot .
#Text=Hitchhiking is widely practiced and quite safe .
#Text=There may be packs of feral dogs roaming any inhabited parts of Majuro .
#Text=Anyone walking or running needs to be ever alert as these dogs frequently attack without provocation .
#Text=Walkers and runners should always carry a stout rod or similar and several rocks for use in thwarting marauding dogs .
#Text=This has become less of a problem in recent years , but is still a danger from time to time .
#Text=Rental cars cost $US 60 per day .
#Text=None of the large commercial rental agencies operate on the island .
#Text=Hotel Robert Reimers has about a dozen cars available .
#Text=The island has four gas stations .
#Text=Ace 's One Stop and Riwut Corner in town , another is just before the bridge dividing Delap from Long Island , and the fourth is just past the airport heading toward Laura .
#Text=See
#Text=The Majuro atoll itself has few things to offer but is a good base for exploration of the surrounding islands .
#Text=The main tourist attraction is Laura Beach on the western tip of the main island about 40km away from town .
#Text=As taxis to Laura Beach are quite expensive the added value of a rental car should not be neglected .
#Text=Eneko Island is a small atoll about 45 minutes away from Uliga by boat .
#Text=Day trips and overnight stays at their small cottages need to be arranged through the Hotel Robert Reimers .
#Text=Camping is also possible .
#Text=Overnight trips are also available to the next atoll , Arno .
#Text=Arno is less developed than Majuro and very beautiful .
#Text=Arrangements can be made at the Happy Hands Handicraft store which shares a parking lot with RRE hotel .
#Text=The boat trip to Arno takes approx. 90 minutes .
#Text=Do
#Text=Scuba diving may be organized through Raycrew located in the first floor of Marshall Islands Resort .
#Text=The staff are friendly and knowledgeable of local dive sites .
#Text=Gear may also be rented here .
#Text=Metered wireless
#Text=Internet access in Majuro is widely available , although occasionally unreliable .
#Text=People may purchase Internet time at the National Telecommunications Administration building or online by following the instructions given when trying to connect .
#Text=Payless Supermarket also has a free wireless connection for customers in its dining area .
#Text=Buy
#Text=The small Formosa Supermarket has groceries and basic supplies but closes early .
#Text=A bigger Payless supermarket is located in Uliga that is usually well stocked .
#Text=K&K Island Pride Supermarket is located in Delap next to the Bank of Guam and has a large fresh produce section .
#Text=Several handicraft stores dot the main part of town .
#Text=A visit to any of these will provide reasonably priced souvenirs .
#Text=On many days you can also find women at these stores making these handicrafts .
#Text=Eat
#Text=Restaurants tend to go through phases in Majuro .
#Text=No place is consistent for more than a few months .
#Text=If a restaurant is really good one week , it may be completely awful the next .
#Text=An always changing workforce contributes greatly to this phenomenon as does the availability of ingredients .
#Text=That being said , asking around about which places are good to eat can help greatly .
#Text=The Tidetable Restaurant attached to the Hotel Robert Reimers is a meeting place for locals as well as expats looking for cheap quality food and Internet access .
#Text=The restaurant overlooks a busy town square as well as the lagoon .
#Text=Try the MEC Blackout - seasoned slices of tuna which just touched a hot pan for a few seconds
#Text=DAR is a small cafe on the backroad of Uliga .
#Text=They have reasonably priced diner fare and some of the best coffee on island .
#Text=It 's a great place to catch up on local gossip as well .
#Text=Won Hai Shien has excellent Chinese food and is located off the main road right next to Uliga Dock .
#Text=Aliang Restaurant is located just next to Won Hai Shien and also has excellent Chinese food , but of a different variety .
#Text=Flame Tree in Delap is a good place to go for pizza before sunset .
#Text=Riwut Corner is a diner that has a selection of American and local foods .
#Text=Marshall Islands Resort has a Sunday brunch with great views of the lagoon .
#Text=Drink
#Text=For nice places full of foreigners , check out the bars at RRE/Tide Table or at Marshall Islands Resort .
#Text=Marshall Islands Club is a local favorite .
#Text=Spacious , with an open air deck situated right on the lagoon .
#Text=The Flame Tree is a very popular bar/club combination with a lively atmosphere .
#Text=The Pub caters to a more upscale crowd .
#Text=The drinks are n't more expensive , but the $ 7 cover charge ( includes free drink ) affects its patronage .
#Text=A well decorated , private VIP section also exists here .
